 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Identity and Access Management (IAM) Delivery Cons Capgemini 8,221 reviews Atlanta, GA 30328 Capgemini 8,221 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job details Job Type Contract Full Job Description Duration :12+Months 
Responsibilities : 
6+ Years of experience in IT and should be aligned with Access Management solutions. 
Of which 4 years of hands-on experience in any of AM products such as Ping Directory, Ping Federate and Ping Access etc. 
Should have experience in installation and configurations of of the above-mentioned product. 
Must have a thorough understanding and work experience for Single Sign-On, Access management, Identity Federation, Multi-factor authentication, Risk / Context-based authentication, On-time provisioning / de-provisioning with any one of the IDM tools. 
Must have a thorough understanding and work experience for technologies such as Header based Single Sign On, SAML, OAuth, Ws-Fed, Ws-Trust, IWA based authentication etc. 
Must have working experience in integration of multiple applications with any one of above-mentioned Access management tools. 
Must have working experience in workflow design and development, role-based access management, creating password policies, 
Hands-On experience with customization of such as UI customization, writing scripts and developing code to fetch assertion values form multiple data sources. 
Experience in integrating directories / Database as Identity store with Access management. 
Knowledge of Sun one LDAP is preferred 
Should be very good Java/J2EE developer 
Thorough in creating technical documentation of Design, Use and Test cases 
Troubleshooting skills are also a must. 
Expertise in J2EE, JSON, REST, SCIM and SOAP-based web services. 
Should be able to work independently as a Sr. Developer, work may require the person to the solution and implement IAM the component. 
Requirements : 
Good collaboration & communication skills, the ability to participate in an interdisciplinary team. 
Strong written communications and documentation experience 
